│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is an assertion failure in                │
│ VPTransformState::get(VPValue *Def, bool NeedsScalar). The assertion checks   │
│ that when we request a single scalar value for a VPValue (NeedsScalar =       │
│ true), it must be safe to do so: either VF is scalar, the value is live-in,   │
│ we have a vector value, its users require more than just the first lane       │
│ (!onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)), or (if onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)) there is exactly    │
│ one cached scalar (lane 0). In the reproducer, Def is a VPReplicateRecipe     │
│ representing a replicated getelementptr (GEP) instruction (%p.4). It was      │
│ executed producing scalars for all lanes (size() == VF), but later when used  │
│ by a PtrAdd VPInstruction that only consumes the first lane,                  │
│ vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def) returns true (because all users of Def only   │
│ use lane 0). This violates the assertion because multiple scalars exist while │
│ callers expect a single one.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug-only vplan │
│ log shows vector.ph and vector.body creation and the crash occurs immediately │
│ when starting to generate vector.body instructions. Stack trace shows         │
│ VPInstruction::generate calling State.get(operand, /*IsScalar*/ true) for     │
│ PtrAdd operands (case VPInstruction::PtrAdd). generate() for PtrAdd           │
│ (VPlanRecipes.cpp:645) asserts onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) and then forces both   │
│ operands to be requested as scalars (NeedsScalar=true). The first operand is  │
│ the replicated GEP recipe. Because its users (PtrAdd) only ever use lane 0,   │
│ vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def) becomes true, triggering the single-scalar    │
│ expectation, but execution previously materialized all lane scalars. This     │
│ mismatch causes the assertion.\n\n3. Root Cause                               │
│ Analysis:\nVPReplicateRecipe::execute (LoopVectorize.cpp lines ~9475+)        │
│ decides the number of lane replicas strictly based on IsUniform, specialized  │
│ store case, or else generates all lanes. It does not take into account that   │
│ although the instruction itself is not marked uniform (IsUniform=false), all  │
│ of its uses may only require lane 0. Later vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)    │
│ relies exclusively on user queries (PtrAdd only first lane), returning true.  │
│ The transform state then assumes there is exactly one scalar cached. Since    │
│ VPReplicateRecipe populated scalars for all VF lanes, the assertion           │
│ fails.\nTherefore, the generation strategy for VPReplicateRecipe is           │
│ inconsistent with the consumption pattern: it should avoid generating         │
│ per-lane scalars when all users only need lane 0, even if IsUniform was       │
│ false.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nModify VPReplicateRecipe::execute so    │
│ that before applying the store special-case or full scalarization, it detects │
│ the situation where all users only need the first lane                        │
│ (vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this)) and generates only lane 0, similar to the  │
│ IsUniform path. This guarantees Data.VPV2Scalars[Def].size()==1 when later    │
│ onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def) is true. Patch location:                               │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp lines 9496-9511 (inside       │
│ VPReplicateRecipe::execute after handling IsUniform).\n\nEdit diff            │
│ (conceptual):\n--- before\n  if (IsUniform) {\n                               │
│ State.ILV->scalarizeInstruction(UI, this, VPLane(0), State);\n    return;\n   │
